        <p>Kraken represents a different philosophy in the crypto exchange world. While competitors chase features and listings, Kraken has doubled down on security and regulatory compliance since its 2011 founding. Understanding this positioning helps determine if Kraken aligns with your priorities.</p>

        <h5>The Security-First Philosophy</h5>
        <p>Kraken's founding team came from security backgrounds, and it shows. They've never been hacked - a remarkable claim in an industry where exchange hacks are almost routine. They pioneered proof of reserves audits, allowing cryptographic verification that customer funds are fully backed. When FTX collapsed in 2022 due to commingled funds, Kraken's proof of reserves became a major selling point. This security focus isn't marketing - it's embedded in their operations.</p>

        <h5>The US Compliance Advantage</h5>
        <p>Unlike Binance (which relegated US users to a separate platform) or many exchanges (which simply block US access), Kraken has invested heavily in US regulatory compliance. They're registered with FinCEN, licensed in most states, and operate transparently within US law. For American crypto investors, this matters - you can use Kraken without VPNs, receive proper tax documents, and have legal recourse if issues arise.</p>

        <h5>Trade-offs to Consider</h5>
        <p>Kraken's security and compliance focus comes with trade-offs. They list fewer coins (200+) than Binance (350+) because they're more selective about listings. Their fees (0.16%/0.26%) are competitive but not the lowest. The interface, especially Kraken Pro, can be complex for beginners. If you want every possible altcoin or the absolute lowest fees, other exchanges may suit you better.</p>

        <h5>The Target User</h5>
        <p>Kraken is best suited for: security-conscious investors who prioritize asset safety, US-based traders wanting a compliant exchange, long-term holders who value proof of reserves, users who want futures/margin with proper regulation, and those willing to pay slightly more for peace of mind. If you're a day trader counting every basis point or an altcoin speculator, you might find better options elsewhere.</p>
